    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you on the doctor stuff but i really don't want to deal with all the appointments anymore. i read online that high doses of garlic extract actually have very strong anti-platelet effects. if i just took like 3000mg of garlic a day and drank a big kale smoothie every morning, wouldn't that be enough to keep my blood thin without needing the warfarin? it seems much safer than those chemicals.",
